### Page routing
- Register all route mappings in `PageRouter` inside `core/router/page_router.dart`
- Create `core/router/` with:
  - `page_name.dart` — route name constants
  - `page_router.dart` — `PageRouter.routes` map

#### Routing convention
- All routes must use named routes
- Register pages with `PageName.<route>` constants only

#### Naming convention
- Every page has a route constant on `PageName`
- Use **lowerCamelCase** for route constants (Dart style for const fields)
- Do not use UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for route constants

#### Do not
- Do not use anonymous navigation like `MaterialPageRoute(...)`
- Do not hardcode string routes like `'/login'` at call sites

#### Example
```dart
// core/router/page_name.dart
class PageName {
  static const String login = '/login';
  static const String home = '/home';
}

// core/router/page_router.dart
class PageRouter {
  static Map<String, WidgetBuilder> routes = {
    PageName.login: (context) => const LoginPage(),
    PageName.home: (context) => const HomePage(),
  };
}

// Navigate
Navigator.of(context).pushNamed(PageName.login);
```
